AKURE – In preparation for its national convention, Social Democratic Party (SDP) in Ondo State has conducted delegates election in Akure, the Ondo State capital. The election was conducted during a well-attended congress of the party on Thursday so that they would be able to participate in the party’s national convention which will hold in line with Independent National Electoral Commission’s directive that all political parties must organise and conclude all their activities on or before June 3, 2022. Members and delegates of the party from 18 local government areas of the state were present while the election was presided over by a national officer of the party and monitored by the officials of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) for proper documentation and authentication. -Advertisement- The Presiding officer at the congress, Hon. Adoko Light, from the National Secretariat of the party in Abuja, commended members and delegates of the party on the peaceful manner they conducted themselves before, during and after the election. He also appreciated the efforts of the members of the state executive of the party in solidifying the party against all odds. Adoko said: “I will like to commend the executive members under the leadership of Hon. Stephen Adewale for their efforts and zeal in making this a reality with the manner at which you organised the Congress, which is an indication of better things to come in the nearest time. “This is an indication that our party has moved to the next level politically and shows we are almost there.” Addressing newsmen after the election, the state Chairman of the party, Hon Stephen Adewale, assured and prospective members that there’s room enough for all and promised a level playing field for all. POLL He said: “I want to assure all our members and those intending to join us that we shall give all equal hands in the scheme of things for a better outing come 2023.”